V[[File:Rainer Forst 2014.jpg|right|thumb|Rainer Forst (2014)]]\u000a'''Rainer Forst''' (born August 15, 1964, [[Wiesbaden]]) is a German [[philosophy|philosopher]] and [[political theory|political theorist]], and was named the "most important political philosopher of his generation" in 2012, when he won the [[Gottfried Wilhelm Leibniz Prize]].<ref>[http://cms.frankfurt-live.com/front_content.php?idcat=10&idart=57018 Frankfurt-Live, \u201eWichtigster politischer Philosoph\u201c seiner Generation: DFG würdigt Leibniz-Preisträger Rainer Forst] Accessed on February 28, 2012</ref>  Currently he is Professor of Political Theory at the Department for Social Sciences,<ref>[http://www.gesellschaftswissenschaften.uni-frankfurt.de/rforst1 Homepage of Rainer Forst], Accessed on August 21, 2007</ref> [[Johann Wolfgang Goethe University]] in [[Frankfurt]]. He is often identified with the newest generation of scholars associated with the [[Frankfurt School]] of [[critical theory]].<ref>[http://www.phil.uu.nl/%7Ejoel/research/publications/3rdGeneration.htm The "Third Generation" of the Frankfurt School] by Joel Anderson, Accessed on August 16, 2006</ref>  He received his doctorate under the supervision of [[Jürgen Habermas]] in 1993.\u000a\u000aHis main areas of research are political theory, [[pragmatism]], tolerance, and political and social justice.  His first book in English, ''Contexts of Justice'', incorporated elements of Anglo-American [[liberalism|liberal theory]] and [[communitarianism]] with German critical and [[social theory]].\u000a\u000a==Publications==\u000a* ''Kontexte der Gerechtigkeit. Politische Philosophie jenseits von Liberalismus und Kommunitarismus.'' 1994, 1996 und 2004, Suhrkamp Verlag. English Title (von John M. M. Farrell): ''Contexts of Justice. Political Philosophy beyond Liberalism and Communitarianism'', Berkeley. Los Angeles: University of California Press, 2002.\u000a* ''Toleranz. Philosophische Grundlagen und gesellschaftliche Praxis einer umstrittenen Tugend''. 2000, Campus Verlag (Herausgeber). (In German)\u000a* ''Toleranz im Konflikt. Geschichte, Gehalt und Gegenwart eines umstrittenen Begriffs''. 2003, Suhrkamp Verlag. (In German)\u000a* ''Das Recht auf Rechtfertigung. Elemente einer konstruktivistischen Theorie der Gerechtigkeit''. 2007, Suhrkamp Verlag. (In German); ''The right to justification: elements of a constructivist theory of justice''.  2012, Columbia University Press.\u000a\u000a==See also==\u000a* [[Critical Theory]]\u000a\u000a==References==\u000a<references/>\u000a\u000a==Further reading==\u000a*{{Citation | last = Guillaume | first = Xavier | contribution = The right to justification: towards a critical theory of justice and democracy. An interview with Rainer Forst. | editor-last1 = Browning | editor-first1 = Gary | editor-last2 = Dimova-Cookson | editor-first2 = Maria | editor-last3 = Prokhovnik | editor-first3 = Raia | editorlink3 = Raia Prokhovnik | title = Dialogues with contemporary political theorists | pages = 105\u2013120 | publisher = Palgrave Macmillan | location = Houndsmill, Basingstoke, Hampshire New York | year = 2012 | isbn = 9780230303058 }}\u000a\u000a==External links==\u000a*[http://www.justitia-amplificata.de/en/team/rainer-forst.html Official University Hompepage] {{de icon}}\u000a__notoc__\u000a{{Authority control}}\u000a\u000a{{DEFAULTSORT:Forst, Rainer}}\u000a[[Category:1964 births]]\u000a[[Category:Frankfurt School]]\u000a[[Category:German philosophers]]\u000a[[Category:Goethe University Frankfurt faculty]]\u000a[[Category:German male writers]]\u000a[[Category:German political scientists]]\u000a[[Category:German political theorists]]\u000a[[Category:Living people]]\u000a[[Category:Political philosophers]]\u000a\u000a{{Germany-academic-bio-stub}}
